","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert was born in 1504, his father, John Freston, was 53 and his mother, Agnes Frankis, was 37. He married Mrs Robert Freston about 1586, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1504–":"1504–Surnud","1488–Male":"1488–Surnud","1504–Male":"1504–Surnud","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1560–Female":"1560–Surnud","1565–Female":"1565–Surnud","1587–Female":"1587–Surnud","1514–1557":"1514–1557","1452–Male":"1452–Surnud","1468–Female":"1468–Surnud","abt. 1514":"umbes 1514","18 May 1587":"18. mai 1587","1560":"1560","1514":"1514","1557":"1557","1468":"1468","Abt 1487":"umbes 1487","1587":"1587","1565":"1565","1488":"1488","1520":"1520","1452":"1452","1504":"1504","Reden Hall, Suff, Eng":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mendham, Norfolk, England":"Mendham, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1504–":"1504–Kuollut","1488–Male":"1488–Kuollut","1504–Male":"1504–Kuollut","1520–Male":"1520–Kuollut","1560–Female":"1560–Kuollut","1565–Female":"1565–Kuollut","1587–Female":"1587–Kuollut","1514–1557":"1514–1557","1452–Male":"1452–Kuollut","1468–Female":"1468–Kuollut","abt. 1514":"noin 1514","18 May 1587":"18